=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Convert the appropriately brominated chloro-azaindole fragment (the bromide corresponding to the target bicyclic unit, e.g. bromo-chloro-1H-pyrrolopyridine) to the matching boronic ester by Miyaura borylation (B2pin2, Pd catalyst) to give the chloro-azaindolyl-Bpin intermediate | Step 2: Suzuki-couple that boronate with 4-chloro-2-fluoro-5-bromopyrimidine to obtain 4-chloro-2-fluoro-5-(chloro-azaindolyl)pyrimidine, i.e. the full heteroaryl core with the target azaindole fragment installed | Step 3: Protect trans-(1R,2S)-2-(aminomethyl)cyclohexan-1-amine on the ring NH2 as Boc to give BocNH-[C@@H]1CCCC[C@H]1CH2NH2 | Step 4: Displace the pyrimidine 4-Cl of the Step 2 intermediate with the free aminomethyl group of the Step 3 chiral amine (SNAr, base, heat) to give the Boc-protected precursor BocNH[C@@H]1CCCC[C@H]1CNc1nc(-c2c[nH]c3ncc(Cl)cc23)ncc1F | Step 5: Remove Boc (TFA or HCl/dioxane) to furnish N[C@@H]1CCCC[C@H]1CNc1nc(-c2c[nH]c3ncc(Cl)cc23)ncc1F.

